President Barack Obama issued a statement on Haitian Flag Day, congratulating those who celebrate it. He highlighted the historical connection between Haiti and the United States, noting how freedmen from Haiti aided American patriots during the Siege of Savannah and how Haiti declared its independence in 1803. While celebrating the Haitian flag, President Obama also acknowledged the ongoing efforts in Haiti to rebuild and recover from the devastating earthquake. He expressed support for the Haitian government and people, emphasizing that they have a friend and partner in America.